grass fence
Homonym Number:
Word Class: noun
Sense Number:
Definition:a fence made by two electric fence wires at the same height and 1 metre apart, to separate out a strip of herbage between the wires; a strip of unbrowsed grass beside an electric fence (or between two parallel electric-fence wires) which can act as a barrier to stock when the power is switched off
Origin: [none]
Register:
Register 2:
Domain: [none]
Region: [none]
